# airbyte_destination_clickhouse (Resource)

DestinationClickhouse Resource

## Example Usage

```terraform
resource "airbyte_destination_clickhouse" "my_destination_clickhouse" {
  configuration = {
    additional_properties = "{ \"see\": \"documentation\" }"
    database              = "...my_database..."
    enable_json           = true
    host                  = "...my_host..."
    password              = "...my_password..."
    port                  = "...my_port..."
    protocol              = "https"
    record_window_size    = 4
    tunnel_method = {
      no_tunnel = {
        additional_properties = "{ \"see\": \"documentation\" }"
        tunnel_method         = "NO_TUNNEL"
      }
    }
    username = "...my_username..."
  }
  definition_id = "f7e79763-e821-47f1-9f09-071b66436a92"
  name          = "...my_name..."
  workspace_id  = "18cdd7db-9638-49f4-915d-c14e35de40fa"
}
```

Import is supported using the following syntax:

In Terraform v1.5.0 and later, the [`import` block](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/language/import) can be used with the `id` attribute, for example:

```terraform

  to = airbyte_destination_clickhouse.my_airbyte_destination_clickhouse
  id = "..."
}
```

The [`terraform import` command](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/cli/commands/import) can be used, for example:

